					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Is there a list of NTSC NES games where the PAL version was adjusted in any way? I'd really be curious which games did changes to the code to accomodate for the 50 Hz since most PAL games simply run slower than their NTSC part.<br /><br />Games where just the music was corrected don't need to be listed since this feature is relatively common, uninteresting and doesn't influence the gameplay.<br /><br />Of course, games where the PAL version was changed in a purely stylistic way that had nothing to do with the technical side (&quot;Contra&quot;/&quot;Probotector&quot;), those don't count either. I'm only interested in technical NTSC/PAL adjustments, not in content-wise changes between the American and European version.</div>

					
