						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">DRW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Now I'm asking which actual games (not homebrew, but the commercial games) changed anything for their PAL conversion and what exactly they changed.</div><br />Now I'm confused. Which did you mean? From least to most strict:<br /><ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha"><li>&quot;Commercial&quot; literally means an item in commerce, which in the case of NES games means sold on cartridge.</li><li>&quot;Not homebrew&quot; means first published before 1997.</li><li>&quot;Official&quot; means licensed by Nintendo.</li></ol><br />Games included on the <em>Action 53</em> compilations meet &quot;commercial&quot; but not &quot;not homebrew&quot; or &quot;official&quot;. Games by Codemasters meet &quot;commercial&quot; and &quot;not homebrew&quot; but not &quot;official&quot;.</div>

